  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (inconsistent requirements)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: This package binds two acceptance requirements whose hemolysis-index thresholds are mutually exclusive — Requirement A mandates RH < 1.0 (model hemolysis must be strictly lower than predicate), while Requirement B mandates RH ≥ 1.0 as a minimum acceptable equivalence margin, making simultaneous satisfaction logically impossible.",
